question: What are genes related to Achromatopsia?
agent_answer:
The genes related to Achromatopsia are:

1. [CNGA3](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:2150)
2. [CNGB3](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:2153)
3. [OPN1MW](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:4206)
4. [OPN1LW](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:9936)
5. [PDE6H](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:8790)
6. [GNAT2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:4394)
7. [ATF6](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:791)

These genes are associated with the development and function of the visual system.
